**My Analysis of the Administrative Unit Change for "Xã Bình Khương, Huyện Bình Sơn, Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi"**

Okay, so the user is looking for the new administrative unit corresponding to "Xã Bình Khương, Huyện Bình Sơn, Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi".  My process here is pretty straightforward: I'll dive into the resolutions and new ward data to pinpoint the updated unit.

First things first, I identified the old province and ward:  "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" and "Xã Bình Khương", respectively.  Now I start cross-referencing this information with the available resolutions.

The province resolutions (60-NQ/TW) didn't give me any significant changes, it only stated that after the merger, the province remains "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi".  So, that was simple enough.

Next step: I turned my attention to the other relevant resolutions. "1677/NQ-UBTVQH15: Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" was the key here.  This is where the real work begins.  Inside, I meticulously read through the resolution, particularly the section dealing with "Xã Bình Khương". Bingo! I found the critical line:

> "5. Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của các xã Bình Khương, Bình An và Bình Minh thành xã mới có tên gọi là **xã Bình Minh**."

This clearly states that "Xã Bình Khương" is being merged into the new "Xã Bình Minh".  Excellent!

Now, to solidify this, I'll need to confirm that "Xã Bình Minh" actually exists in the updated data.  I cross-referenced this in the "New wards" list, and there it was:

> `{"ward_code":"21085","ward_name":"Xã Bình Minh","province_name":"Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi"}`

A perfect match!

To be extra cautious, I quickly scanned the rest of the relevant resolution (1677/NQ-UBTVQH15) to make sure there weren't any other factors I needed to consider, especially involving "Huyện Bình Sơn". However, the other lines in the document were about creating different units.

So, the conclusion is: "Xã Bình Khương" in "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" has been absorbed into the newly created "Xã Bình Minh" also in "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi". The confidence in this answer is high because of the explicit statement regarding "Xã Bình Khương" in resolution "1677/NQ-UBTVQH15".
